Windows Forensics – File System, Execution & Data Recovery

File System Basics:

File System:
	•	Organizes raw disk bits into meaningful data
	•	Defines how files are stored, accessed, and interpreted


⸻

FAT File System:

Structure:
	•	Clusters → Smallest storage unit (file = group of clusters)
	•	Directory → Stores file name, start cluster, size
	•	FAT Table → Linked list of clusters (file chain mapping)

Variants:
	•	FAT12 → 12-bit, very small (32MB)
	•	FAT16 → 16-bit, up to 2GB
	•	FAT32 → 28-bit, up to 2TB

Limitations:
	•	Max file size: 4GB
	•	No security or permissions


⸻

exFAT:

•	Designed to replace FAT32 limitations
•	Supports very large files and volumes (up to 128PB)
•	Used in modern USB drives, SD cards
•	Lightweight (no heavy NTFS features)


⸻

NTFS File System:

Features:
	•	Journaling → $LogFile tracks changes
	•	Access Control → File permissions per user
	•	Volume Shadow Copy → File version recovery
	•	Alternate Data Streams → Hidden data in files

Core Structure:
	•	MFT (Master File Table) → Database of all files

Key Artifacts:
	•	$MFT → File records and metadata
	•	$LogFile → File system transactions
	•	$UsnJrnl → File change history (timeline)


⸻

Deleted Files & Recovery:

Deletion Behavior:
	•	File system removes metadata (not actual data)
	•	Data remains until overwritten

Disk Image:
	•	Bit-by-bit copy of storage device
	•	Preserves metadata and evidence
	•	Used for safe forensic analysis

Recovery:
	•	Deleted files can be recovered from unallocated space
	•	Tools identify file signatures automatically


⸻

Execution Artifacts (File System):

Prefetch:
	•	Location: C:\Windows\Prefetch
	•	Stores:
		- Last run time
		- Run count
		- Files used
	•	Strong evidence of execution

Windows Timeline:
	•	Location: C:\Users\<user>\AppData\Local\ConnectedDevicesPlatform\...\ActivitiesCache.db
	•	Stores:
		- Applications used
		- File activity
		- Usage duration

Jump Lists:
	•	Location: C:\Users\<user>\AppData\Roaming\Microsoft\Windows\Recent\AutomaticDestinations
	•	Stores:
		- Recent files per application
		- Execution timestamps

Shortcut Files (.lnk):
	•	Location:
		- C:\Users\<user>\AppData\Roaming\Microsoft\Windows\Recent\
		- C:\Users\<user>\AppData\Roaming\Microsoft\Office\Recent\
	•	Stores:
		- File path
		- Creation → first access
		- Modified → last access

IE/Edge WebCache:
	•	Location: C:\Users\<user>\AppData\Local\Microsoft\Windows\WebCache\WebCacheV*.dat
	•	Stores:
		- Browsing history
		- Local file access (file:// paths)


⸻

USB & Device Artifacts:

SetupAPI Logs:
	•	Location: C:\Windows\inf\setupapi.dev.log
	•	Stores:
		- Device ID
		- Serial number
		- First connection time
		- Last connection time

Shortcut Files (.lnk):
	•	Can reveal USB volume name, type, serial number


⸻

Key Notes:

•	FAT → simple, no security
•	NTFS → advanced, forensic-rich
•	MFT = central database of files
•	Deleted ≠ erased (recoverable until overwritten)
•	Combine multiple artifacts for accurate timeline